Renovatio affedationis decimarum garbalium ecclefiae commensalis de Rothemaye ab Episcopo cum consensu capituli concessa Willelmo domino de Abirnethy‚ Rothemay et Saltoun et Alex- andro magistro Saltoun ejus filio, pro 19 annis. Solvendo annuatim L.40‚ et dictam ecclefiam reparando et supportando. Testibus Georgio comite de Huntlie, magistro Georgio Gordoun constabulario de Baidyenocht, dominis et magistris Magno Vause rectore de Jy, Johanne Gor- doun vicario de Keth, Hugone Cragy, Willelmo Wyisman notariis et domino Thema Wallace vicario de Spyne. Apud ecclesiam cathedralem, 16 Aprilis 1540.

Tack of the personage of Rothemay and of the personage and vicarage of Keth set be the Bischop with consent of the cheptour to Alexander Lord Saltoun for nyneten yeris. Payand thairfor yeirlie 460 merkis to the Bischop at twa termis Sanct Serfis day and All hallowmess, and to the vicar penfionar of Keitht his yeirlie penfioun‚ and that in confideratioun of the inlaik of corps presents, pasche fynes, umaist claithis and utheris profeittis of the said vicar-age of Keitht deducit be the trubill of the kirk laitlie maid, quhilk was the maist part of the profeit of the said vicarage 3 and the said Lord to upbald, beit and mend during the forsaidis yeirs the queir of Rothemay in theking and utheris necessaris reparatioun concerning the personage thereos upoun his awin costis. At Spyne and Elgin, 28 Maii 1570.

Carta feodifirmae ab Episcopo cum consensu capituli facta Alexandro Keyr Makyntosy, terra- rum ecclefiasticarum de Rothymurchus in vic: de Innernes; Reddendo 24 mercas annuatim donec et quousque dictus Alexander vel ejus heredes infeodaverint Episcopum et capitulum de decem libratis terrarum de Rege tenendarum, in loco competenti in aquis de Spey et Nys, inter lc glen de Rothes et mare, vel inter baroniam de Lethyn et mare, vel saltem in dieta baronia et non altius jacentium; quo facto, dictus Alexander habebit dictas terras de Rothymurchus in verum excambium pro dictis decem libratis terrae, Reddendo unum germen abiegnum s1 peta- tur. Apud Elgin, 4 Septembris 1464.

Confirmatio ab Episcopo data cartae venditionis ab Alano Keyr McKyntosy de Rathamurcous conceffae magistro Georgio Gordoun constabulario de Ruthven de Baidyenoch, earundem terra- rum de Rathamurcous cum lacu et manerie seu fortalicio, tenendarum de Episcopo sub eisdem conditionibus et cum eadem potestate excambii quae in carta Alexandri continentur; libero tenemento reservato pro tempore vitae dicti Alani.
